<section id="Day1">
<a href="#Day1"><h2>Day1:Arrival in Delhi</h2></a>
<p>On reaching Delhi airport, meet our IHPL representative who assists you while you take a transfer to the hotel. Check-in to the hotel and <br />.
then leave for sightseeing around the capital city, Delhi.Begin with a visit to one of the major attractions of Delhi, The Red Fort. The Red Fort<br />
 was built by Shah Jahan, back in 1648. This iconic symbol of the country takes one back to the Mughal era. Later, visit Kingdom of Dreams which<br />
 is the ultimate entertainment destination in Delhi.
The place presents a great blend of India’s culture, heritage, art and crafts. Walk through the culture gully and explore the various colors of India. <br />
After enjoying cultural shows, return to the hotel for dinner and stay overnight at the hotel.
</p>
</section>
<section id="Day2">
<a href="#Day2"><h2>Day2:Delhi City Tour - Agra</h2></a>
<p>After having your breakfast in the morning, go for sightseeing around Delhi. Visit famous attractions of Delhi such as Akshardham temple, Lotus Temple.<br />
 Return to the hotel for lunch. Later, start driving towards Agra. On reaching Agra, check-in at the hotel.
You can spend the rest of the evening at leisure or take a stroll around the place. Later, return to the hotel for dinner. Have a comfortable stay at night.</p>
</section> 
<section id="Day3">
<a href="#Day3"><h2>Day3:Agra Sightseeing - Delhi</h2></a>
<p>Begin this morning with delicious breakfast and then leave for sightseeing around the City of Love, Agra. Visit Agra Fort, Itimad-Ud-Daulah and Taj Mahal - One of the Seven Wonder of the World.
Witness the rich past of the Mughal Era and flip back the pages of the history. Later,start driving<br />
 back to Delhi. Stay overnight at the hotel.
</p>
</section>
<section id="Day4">
<a href="#Day4"><h2>Day4:Delhi Sightseeing & Departure</h2></a>
<p>This morning, have your breakfast and then leave for a visit to major attractions like Raj Ghat, Rashtrapati Bhavan, Parliament House, India Gate <br />
(War Memorial Arch), and Laxminarayan Temple.All these attractions hold much importance and they represent the capital city Delhi at its best. Later,<br />
 visit other attractions like Qutub Minar and Humayun tomb. Later, drive towards the airport for your onward journey. The tour ends here.
</p>
